President Biden has announced the first-ever U.S. National Strategy to Counter Antisemitism, which is being praised by leaders across the country. The strategy outlines a whole-of-society approach, organized in four pillars of action, to address key themes and threats raised by over 1,000 stakeholders. It includes over 100 meaningful actions government agencies will take to increase understanding of antisemitism, protect Jewish institutions and communities, reverse the normalization of antisemitism, and build cross-community solidarity. The strategy also includes over 100 calls-to-action for Congress, state and local governments, tech companies, and others to counter antisemitism. Leaders and organizations are commending President Biden for his commitment to combating antisemitism and protecting the Jewish community.